Telemachus is a fork of SideScreen, originally created by Tran Vuong Quoc Dat
and developed with the SideScreen contributors:
https://github.com/tranvuongquocdat/SideScreen

SideScreen established the foundational virtual-display, capture, encoding,
ADB/TCP transport, Android decoding, wireless-pairing, and touch-input
implementation used by this fork. The original SideScreen copyright and MIT
License notice are preserved in LICENSE.

Telemachus uses private, unsupported macOS CGVirtualDisplay APIs to create a
virtual display. Those APIs are not licensed or endorsed as a public Apple SDK,
may change without notice, and may limit App Store distribution.
